name: Yeah Baby Canyon
description:
Introduction

Yeah-baby Canyon is a short drive from Brisbane, making for a great day trip. The canyon includes 2x30m, 1x20m, 1x7m, and a few optional 5-10m pitches. The canyon also boasts a sweet slide at the end (picture top right).

Usually dry, a very small catchment.

Approach

Descent

Extremely dodgy natural anchors inplace. Caution all who dare enter.

Exit

The walk out follows the stunning wide Guanaba Creek, hugged by a vibrant palm tree rainforest. Following this is a walk up a firetrail from the creek straight back to a car. A 15-minute car swap is required.

Red tape

Access to the canyon requires crossing private property. The exit requires crossing the Guanaba Indigenous Protected Area which requires permission ahead of time. Consequently, due to the sensitivity the canyon should not be completed.
